 <font color=#333333>(6/11/02 7:27:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=237.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Fixing Burnout by Raising Pet Haste Cap</span><hr size=1> I think <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Cyricus</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> has pretty conclusively demonstrated that that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Burnout IV</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is useless, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Muzzle of Mardu</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> only marginally useful for non-Epicked mages in his thread, <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showMessage?topicID=1327.topic">Haste cap - Part III - Summary</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  Before <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->'s attention completely drifts away from us, the question is, what would be an adequate and fair solution?<br>
<br>
The problem seems to be, as best as I understand, is that pets have a haste cap of 60%.  The epic pet appears to have 10% built in haste.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Burnout III</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> has 60% haste all by itself, which hits that cap.  Thus <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Burnout IV</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which has 65% haste, is a complete waste, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Muzzle of Mardu</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, at about 14%, is also wasted on a buffed pet.  The legendary <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ancient: Burnout V</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> would appear to be a cruel joke under these circumstrances, with its supposed 80% haste, and therefore is any wonder that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Frenzied Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, with its claim of 99% haste, seems to have little effect on damage output.<br>
<br>
Worse, the same data also seems to suggest a cap on strength as well, which again partially explains the poor performance of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Frenzied Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
The obvious solution is to raise the haste cap for pets, to at least 100%, if not 115%, in order to see improvement with all the burnouts plus <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Muzzle of Mardu</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Given the improvement in pet damage output that would yield, however, the 60% haste cap may have been introduced purposely when the base damage on <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Greater Vocaration</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Epic Pets</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> was increase by 10 points, in order to at least initially limit its impact incase <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> had misjudged.<br>
<br>
For melee, according to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Cyricus</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, the epic pet does about 36 average per hit with a 31 delay, and GV:E does about 30 average damage with 34 base delay.  With the current 60% haste cap, delay gets not much better than 20 <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (rounding a little for ease of estimation)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
If the haste cap were raised to 100%, then with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Burnout III</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> plus <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Muzzle of Mardu</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> should reduce the delay to just under 18 for the epic pet, and just over 19 for GV:E.  While noticeable, not obviously game breaking.  With <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Burnout IV</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> plus <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Muzzle</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, the delay for epics with be a tad over 17, and for GV:E just under 19 delay.  Also not earth shattering.  For the rare mage with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ancient Burnout V</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> plus <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Muzzle</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, the delays would be just under 16 for the epic, and still over 17 delay for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> GV:E</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  I see nothing broken about either one, as none represents even a 10% increase in pet melee damage output, which is less than half the damage output of a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> generally.<br>
<br>
The question arises then, since we appear to opening the door to fixes in the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, albeit indirectly by raising the haste cap, if this isn't the appropriate time to begin addressing pet damage on raids.<br>
<br>
Here, I really have to defer to my elders, especially log fanatics, as I really have no solid experience to judge raid damage output of pets.  But from what I read on the boards, the general consensus is that if a fix is needed, then ATK is the solution.  Perhaps <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Burnout IV</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> could have a modest attack component, not sure exactly what, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ancient Burnout V</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a more significant ATK bonus.  As the latter is only available to strong raiders, that seems entirely appropriate.<br>
<br>
However, another can of worms that suggests itself at this point are the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician Class AA Skills</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Clearly, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Frenzied Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is pointless with a 60% haste cap, but then it is not entirely clear it would be worthwhile if the haste cap were lifted.  Suppose <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Frenzied Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> plus <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Muzzle</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is 115% haste, then from haste alone the damage output is not even doubled compared to the current 60% cap, not counting ATK.  How much extra damage should the supposed +200 ATK yield?  I don't know.<br>
<br>
The best possible case is that it hit for full every time, that is it would roughly double its average damage per hit.  At the same time, assuming it started with BO3 and Muzzle, the increased haste would yield less than 23% extra damage.<br>
<br>
Bottom line is, assuming everything is golden, we are talking about less than 150% extra melee damage for only 36 seconds, or 30 DPS * 1.5 * 36 seconds = 1620 extra damage, less than two decent nukes.  Less than letting the pet melee for a minute longer.<br>
<br>
And that is assuming that +200 ATK means hitting for nearly max every time, which I doubt.<br>
<br>
Besides which, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Frenzied Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> feels <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>wrong</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> to me.  If I want to burn something down, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Karana</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> has already granted me access to many fine nukes that accomplish this exact goal.  In 36 seconds, should I care to burn down my mana bar, I could cast 4 <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Shock of Fiery Blades</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Yes, the spells can be resisted, and yes, against magic resisted mobs, melee is better, but using <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Frenzied Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> only makes sense if you <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>know</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> the fight will or must be over in the next 36 seconds, otherwise it is better to let the current pet continue to melee if there is more than minute left to the fight.<br>
<br>
What seems obviously lacking to me in the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician Class Skills</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is some form of regular <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, the normal kind that lasts 15 minutes, and does not kill your pet.  With a 72 or even 144 minute timer, a new <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Improved Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> skill would last 15 minutes, and make a real difference in a long fight.<br>
<br>
Not sure what <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Improved Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> should do.  It could either modify the next casting of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, or act like a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> spell by itself.  Maybe it should add +10 ATK per level of the next ordinary <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> spell cast, i.e. +30 ATK for BO3, +40 ATK for BO4, etc.  Whereas I am not sure what the exact impact of that ATK would be, based on what I have seen else I do not think it would be game breaking.  Heck, it could even have three levels, each adding +5 ATK per BO level cast (5/10/15) and cost 5/10/15 AA to get those levels.  There's a reasonable 30 AA sink right there, and could well create a demand for high level mages on raids.<br>
<br>
Anyway, there are several things I admit to being ignorant about.  First of, what are the raid target where our pets cannot melee effectively?  What is the effect of ATK on damage output?  How much ATK would be required to make pets useful against those raid targets?  And would it break exping on a 72 minute timer, or should it be a 144 minute timer instead.<br>
<br>
I've babbled enough, and look forward to your comments, especially those of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Cyricus</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, for whose data and analysis I am grateful.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Senior ArchAbuser of EZCodes</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
